I have been trying to process this and I don’t even know where to begin or how to even write this…. I am completely heartbroken.  You were my brother for over 15 years.  You always told me how much you valued our brotherhood and so did I more than you’ll ever know.  You and I had such a strong bond from the day we met.  You’ve always been such a loyal and caring friend who always put everyone else before yourself no matter what.  You lit up the room with your bright smile and infectious laugh and your love for your family was so special and beautiful. 
You were always there for me during difficult times, constantly checking in on me and also there with me for some of the best moments of my life. You have always been love, light and positivity.  When we we’re together our inside jokes and laughter never stopped…. literally we would laugh for hours on end. I will love you and miss you forever my brother and I’m so grateful for all of the moments we shared together. 
My dearest Allison all my prayers are with you and your family. Sending you all my love. 
🙏🏽🕊️

art·ist
/ˈärdəst/ 
a person skilled at a particular task or occupation.
a performer, such as a singer, actor, or dancer. 

I always use the word “artist” when anyone asks what I do.  I say that because I sing, dance, choreograph, act, direct, produce, shoot photography, edit etc…. They all fall under the umbrella of an Artist.  I also believe you can do anything you want creatively.  You do not need to be pigeonholed into one thing.  Do whatever you want. 
After years of working and writing in the studio and stopping my project during the pandemic I am finally releasing my album.  I am so grateful for everyone involved in this with me and everyone that has been a part of this journey along the way. 
Ready to keep it moving! 
Next drop off the album is 3/22/23

⚡️FORGET YOU ⚡️
STREAMING NOW ON ALL MUSIC PLATFORMS. 
It’s been a life rollercoaster since I wrote this song 4 years ago. It’s finally time to release it out into the world! I was originally supposed to release this in 2020 and then the world shut down and I didn’t release it for obvious reasons. This song came from a place of honesty and growth. Sometimes we find ourselves in situations we know aren’t good for us, but we can’t seem to let go. Through it all, I learned the importance of setting standards for myself and those around me. Every friendship and relationship in our lives is meant to teach us something.  I actually ended up getting the word standards tattooed on my arm because The biggest lesson I learned through all of this is standards, and holding everyone including myself to a higher standard. 
I believe every friendship, and relationship in your life is not an accident.  You are definitely meant to learn from them.  Whether they are there forever or just a season. 
STREAM FORGET YOU NOW ON ALL MUSIC STREAMING PLATFORMS . #bobbynewberry #bobbynewberrymusic #NewMusic #Honesty #Growth #forgetyou

2️⃣ @joespizzanyc SOHO - Fresh out of the oven hot and crispy cheese pizza. 🍕🔥

5️⃣ @thecrownnyc - Best views, iconic setting, stunning rooftop terraces. 🌇🌃
6️⃣ @50bowery hotel - Floor to ceiling windows with stunning views of the city. 🏙️
7️⃣ @dominiqueansel - French toast is EVERYTHING, almond croissant, and my favorite was the matcha coconut flavored cronut, it was sooooo amazing. 🥐🍵
